This paper is primarily focused on deep reinforcement learning (DRL), which is a subfield of machine learning (ML) that combines deep learning and reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary category for ML research. 

The paper also discusses the impact of deterministic implementations on the training process, which is relevant to the broader field of artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. 

The authors specifically study the deep Q-learning algorithm, which is commonly used in robotics and control systems. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible categories. 

Finally, the paper includes experiments on image-based environments, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) could also be a relevant category.
